cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of content caching in wireless networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents online learning methods for predicting content popularity, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The use of Grassmannian prediction model (GPM) and constrained non-negative least squares (NNLS) algorithm also suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the simulation results involve the use of MovieLens dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
